title: SFH chairs Preparatory Task Force on Chinese Medicine Development Committee's first meeting (with photos)
content_text:
p>
    The Preparatory Task Force (PTF) on the Chinese Medicine Development 
    Committee held its first meeting this morning (August 31) to discuss the 
    terms of reference and composition of the Committee, as well as the 
    priorities and direction of the Committee's work in the future. The PTF is chaired by the Secretary for Food and Health, Dr Ko Wing-man. At 
    the meeting, Dr Ko briefed the members on the terms of reference, framework 
    and membership of the existing monitoring organisations and committees

and membership of the existing monitoring organisations and committees 
    related to Chinese medicine for their consideration. Dr Ko said that all members of the PTF have rich experience and knowledge in 
    the Chinese medicine field. He believed the PTF would make valuable comments 
    and suggestions about the Committee's membership and terms of reference, as 
    well as on the way forward for Chinese medicine development in Hong Kong. The PTF was set up on August 14 this year. Members include the Chairman of 
    the Chinese Medicine Council of Hong Kong, Professor Andrew Chan; Chairman

the Chinese Medicine Council of Hong Kong, Professor Andrew Chan; Chairman 
    of the Chinese Medicine Practitioners Board of the Chinese Medicine Council 
    of Hong Kong, Mr Wong Kit; Chairperson of the Hong Kong Registered Chinese 
    Medicine Practitioners Association, Ms Fung Jiu; Chairman of the Hong Kong 
    Chinese Medicine Industry Association, Mr Tommy Li; Council member of the 
    Modernized Chinese Medicine International Association Mr Abraham Chan; 
    Director of the School of Chinese Medicine of the University of Hong Kong,

Director of the School of Chinese Medicine of the University of Hong Kong, Professor Tong Yao; Director of the School of Chinese Medicine of the Chinese University of Hong Kong, Professor Albert Leung; Dean of Chinese Medicine of the Hong Kong Baptist University, Professor Lu Aiping; Permanent Secretary for Food and Health (Health); and the Director of Health. Ends/Friday, August 31, 2012
Issued at HKT 17:16
